headline: 3 Reasons to Sell OTIS and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Over the past six months, Otis’s stock price fell to $88.58. Shareholders have lost 11.5% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 8.6%. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
